2
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:40,020
(Jin Chaoshan)

3
00:00:53,220 --> 00:00:57,620
(I want to apologize
to all my colleagues.)

4
00:00:57,620 --> 00:01:02,180
(I owe you all. I will repay it
in my next life. From: Jin Chaoshan)

5
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:45,580
=Playing Go=

6
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:51,740
=Episode 10=
=A Chance to Make a Comeback=

7
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:03,430
Captain.

8
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,870
Over there.

9
00:03:37,470 --> 00:03:39,190
I should have come out earlier.

10
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:41,870
When I got out,
the fire was still burning.

11
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:17,180
(Move Only When the Time Is Right)

12
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:18,630
That's all for today's class.

13
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:19,470
Class dismissed.

14
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,600
- Let's go.
- Fang Chengdong.

15
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,880
- Come on, let's go.
- Hurry up!

16
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:26,670
Bye-bye.

17
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,270
- Class dismissed.
- Hello, Mr. Zhang.

18
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:29,110
Hello, sir.

19
00:04:29,210 --> 00:04:30,640
- Class is over.
- Hello, Mr. Zhang.

20
00:04:30,650 --> 00:04:31,510
Alright.

21
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:32,510
Mr. Zhang.

22
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:33,510
Mr. Cui.

23
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:34,430
Good news.

24
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,950
I've already found a place.

25
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:38,070
Go see if it works for you.

26
00:04:39,730 --> 00:04:40,580
Alright.

27
00:04:40,580 --> 00:04:41,580
I'll wait outside.

28
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,780
Don't take too long.

29
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:48,940
Chen Xiaoguang, why are you still here?

30
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,660
Mr. Cui.

31
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:53,100
Are you really not going
to teach us anymore?

32
00:04:58,540 --> 00:04:59,820
Who told you that?

33
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:03,340
If you want to learn,

34
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:05,860
I'll always be here to teach you.

35
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:08,380
Once the master class starts,

36
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:09,900
I'll take you there.

37
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,780
- Sound good?
- Okay.

38
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:13,460
Alright, head on home now.

39
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:19,860
Goodbye, Mr. Cui.

40
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,900
What do you think of this place?

41
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:02,140
Isn't it beautiful?

42
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:04,940
Far from the noise of the world,

43
00:06:05,260 --> 00:06:07,300
basked in the charm of nature.

44
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,980
Totally worthy of a master.

45
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:22,500
This place

46
00:06:23,340 --> 00:06:24,180
is quite nice.

47
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:25,580
Alright.

48
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:26,500
Let's go with it.

49
00:06:26,780 --> 00:06:27,620
Great.

50
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:28,980
That's all I needed to hear.

51
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:30,420
I'll go negotiate the deal.

52
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,020
I'll get it.

53
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:34,020
I should get going.

54
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:38,660
Hello?

55
00:06:39,620 --> 00:06:40,660
What?

56
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:08,860
Why are you still here?

57
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:11,140
I want to bring my brother home.

58
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:13,700
Can you help me?

59
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:15,780
Your brother?

60
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:17,660
What do you mean?

61
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,540
His ashes are still at the funeral home.

62
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,220
I thought about it all night.

63
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:26,700
I can't go back alone.

64
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:29,220
How would I explain it to my dad?

65
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:32,020
How did you find out about all this?

66
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,140
The radio.

67
00:07:34,940 --> 00:07:36,380
There was a show on yesterday.

68
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,060
A cop mentioned it.

69
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:40,220
What show was it?

70
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:48,580
Listen to me.

71
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:50,980
Tell your dad

72
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,780
you and your brother

73
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:53,900
got separated.

74
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:55,180
You had no idea where he went.

75
00:07:55,460 --> 00:07:56,340
Think about it.

76
00:07:56,340 --> 00:07:57,980
If you really brought him back,

77
00:07:58,290 --> 00:07:59,730
how would you explain it to your dad?

78
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:01,520
That he fell to his death?
Died from illness?

79
00:08:01,530 --> 00:08:03,140
You'd only break his heart.

80
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:06,380
But, I can't let my brother die
without a proper burial.

81
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:08,660
I don't want him to become a lost soul.

82
00:08:17,020 --> 00:08:19,140
Don't you think
it's strange this radio show

83
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:20,340
aired that story?

84
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:22,500
Maybe that cop arranged it

85
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:24,020
to lure you out.

86
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:25,180
So, I need your help.

87
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:26,220
How am I supposed to help?

88
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,540
You'll think of something.

89
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:28,980
You always do, don't you?

90
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:46,340
Alright.

91
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:48,500
Cui Ye.

92
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,260
You're not going to help me?

93
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:51,900
Fine. I'll go on my own.

94
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,660
I have to bring my brother home.

95
00:08:58,620 --> 00:09:00,020
Go back for now.

96
00:09:00,020 --> 00:09:01,220
Don't go anywhere.

97
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:06,020
If you trust me, wait for me to find you.

98
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:09,780
Figure out what to tell your dad.

99
00:09:26,540 --> 00:09:27,380
Hello?

100
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:28,860
I'd like to ask something.

101
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:31,980
Do you have the contact number
for that city radio show?

102
00:09:39,310 --> 00:09:42,380
I heard you had a police officer
on the show yesterday.

103
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:43,940
It was a really good episode.

104
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,300
But, I didn't catch the whole thing.

105
00:09:50,380 --> 00:09:51,500
Will there be a replay?

106
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:53,700
What time?

107
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:32,100
(Lanshui City Funeral Home)

108
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:32,820
(IC Card Phone)

109
00:12:01,140 --> 00:12:02,140
Uncle.

110
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:04,900
It's me, Xiasheng.

111
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,380
Well...

112
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,620
I just called home but no one picked up.

113
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,500
Where's my dad?

114
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:31,380
What's wrong?

115
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:41,060
What happened?

116
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,340
I...

117
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:05,100
I just lost my dad.

118
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:16,740
Brother...

119
00:15:17,180 --> 00:15:18,540
I brought my brother home.

120
00:15:42,820 --> 00:15:43,900
Stop crying.

121
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:47,860
Stop crying.

122
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:50,420
Stop crying. That's not ashes.

123
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:52,060
Open it and take a good look.

124
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:53,300
That's not ashes.

125
00:16:27,260 --> 00:16:28,300
I'm sorry.

126
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,060
Why?

127
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,860
Why did you lie to me?

128
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,700
I'm sorry.

129
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,700
The police are watching everything.

130
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,620
I can't show up.

131
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:06,660
If this turns out

132
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:08,460
to be a trap,

133
00:17:08,980 --> 00:17:10,460
then I'm done for if I show up.

134
00:17:12,580 --> 00:17:13,820
If they catch me,

135
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:16,420
even if I say nothing,

136
00:17:17,060 --> 00:17:18,540
they'll still find you.

137
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:20,700
And then, it's game over for you too.

138
00:17:24,580 --> 00:17:25,940
So what?

139
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,900
I have nothing left anyway.

140
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:36,740
Get up.

141
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:38,900
Your brother gave his life for yours.

142
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,460
You want to get caught that badly?

143
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,060
Go ahead and get caught then.

144
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:45,900
Might as well call the police yourself.

145
00:17:46,060 --> 00:17:47,260
Turn yourself in.

146
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:52,620
What do you mean
he gave his life for mine?

147
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,620
They were going to pick you.

148
00:18:03,340 --> 00:18:04,780
You brother went in instead.

149
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,180
Think about it.

150
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:25,660
You haven't lost everything.

151
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:30,780
Then, what do I still have?

152
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:34,260
You have money.

153
00:18:34,540 --> 00:18:35,820
You have plenty of time.

154
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:37,740
You have a second chance.

155
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,420
Seriously?

156
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:48,780
Despair

157
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,980
is what my son went through.

158
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,540
No one could cure him.

159
00:18:54,420 --> 00:18:56,580
He just suffered until the end.

160
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,620
Do you see the difference?

161
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:04,220
We should

162
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:06,220
live for the people who care about us.

163
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:10,060
They're already gone.

164
00:19:10,580 --> 00:19:12,620
Then, live on for the dead!

165
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:38,460
Have you thought it through?

166
00:19:42,180 --> 00:19:43,580
I want to be alone for a while.

167
00:19:44,180 --> 00:19:45,220
I'm fine.

168
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,780
Go home and start over.

169
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:55,500
You have a long road ahead.

170
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:20,660
Dad.

171
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:22,580
When is Mom coming home?

172
00:20:24,340 --> 00:20:25,260
Soon.

173
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,740
What happened to your face?

174
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:40,820
It's nothing.

175
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,220
I just bumped into something.

176
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:51,020
Today, we're honored
to have a special guest with us.

177
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:53,540
Detective Cui Wei from
the city's Criminal Police Division.

178
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,460
It's Captain Cui.

179
00:20:58,660 --> 00:20:59,500
Yan.

180
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:01,540
Did you tell Lin she was going

181
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:03,220
to the Experimental Middle School?

182
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:07,660
What exactly did she tell you?

183
00:21:07,980 --> 00:21:09,220
Tell me about it.

184
00:21:12,420 --> 00:21:14,980
She said she doesn't want
to go to Experimental Middle School.

185
00:21:16,860 --> 00:21:19,380
But Uncle and Aunt contacted someone

186
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:20,740
and insisted she go.

187
00:21:47,940 --> 00:21:49,060
(Many of our listeners)

188
00:21:49,060 --> 00:21:51,180
(have shared valuable feedback with us.)

189
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:53,900
(I would like to thank all of you.)

190
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:56,340
(Your support helps us
keep getting better.)

191
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:58,420
(After the music, we will bring you)

192
00:21:58,660 --> 00:21:59,900
("Big Things in a Small Town.")

193
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,260
(For the citizens of this city,)

194
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:14,060
(no issue is ever too small.)

195
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:15,060
Hello, everyone.

196
00:22:15,060 --> 00:22:15,940
I am the host

197
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:18,580
who care about your issues
like they are my own, Le.

198
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,900
As always on our show,

199
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:23,660
we are ready to take calls
from our enthusiastic listeners

200
00:22:23,660 --> 00:22:25,860
and help solve problems
you face in life.

201
00:22:25,860 --> 00:22:27,420
(Lanshui City Radio)

202
00:22:27,420 --> 00:22:29,780
The signal light in front of me
is already on.

203
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:31,420
Let us listen

204
00:22:31,420 --> 00:22:33,540
to what this caller is dealing with.

205
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:36,620
Hello, caller.

206
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:38,860
I think

207
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:42,060
your radio station
is being very irresponsible.

208
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:44,540
Yesterday,

209
00:22:45,380 --> 00:22:47,140
your show "Life On the Line"

210
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:49,540
invited someone from
the city police department,

211
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:52,220
Captain Cui Wei of
the Criminal Police Division.

212
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:55,260
How could you let someone like that
be on your show?

213
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,140
He is two-faced.

214
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:00,540
He talks like a decent person on air,

215
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:02,860
but off air, he abuses his power.

216
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:05,260
He used his power to get
his child into an elite school.

217
00:23:06,060 --> 00:23:07,300
That means other students

218
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:08,620
will lose their rightful

219
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:09,860
school spots.

220
00:23:10,460 --> 00:23:11,860
This is despicable.

221
00:23:13,140 --> 00:23:14,820
You need to investigate him.

222
00:23:19,580 --> 00:23:21,140
Alright, caller.

223
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:22,740
We have noted what you reported.

224
00:23:31,980 --> 00:23:32,900
Captain.

225
00:23:34,060 --> 00:23:34,940
Captain.

226
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:37,290
The cigarettes and liquor we found
outside the funeral home.

227
00:23:37,340 --> 00:23:38,500
The tech team said

228
00:23:38,700 --> 00:23:41,300
the fingerprints matched one set
from Qin Xiaoming's phone.

229
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:43,980
We traced the origin
based on the labels on the items.

230
00:23:44,140 --> 00:23:45,700
Both came from Dantong, Liaojiang.

231
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:56,140
(Miner)

232
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,100
Dantong...

233
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:00,220
Check if there are any mines in Dantong.

234
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:02,620
Any kind of mine will do.

235
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,380
There are quite a few.

236
00:24:07,380 --> 00:24:08,380
More than ten.

237
00:24:15,340 --> 00:24:17,620
Look into any
that have been restructured.

238
00:24:18,660 --> 00:24:21,300
In the past few years, four mines
have gone through restructuring.

239
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:22,900
Only one of them still requires

240
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:24,300
underground operations.

241
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:25,160
Dongfeng Coal Mine.

242
00:24:25,170 --> 00:24:26,660
One year ago, they changed ownership.

243
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:29,140
It went from a collective-owned entity
to a private business.

244
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,580
See for yourself.

245
00:24:39,340 --> 00:24:40,620
A student's parent

246
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,980
reported you through that radio station.

247
00:24:43,340 --> 00:24:44,900
They said you abused your power

248
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,620
to pull strings
for your child's education.

249
00:24:46,980 --> 00:24:47,860
You abused your power

250
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:48,860
for personal gain.

251
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:50,460
This has tarnished our reputation.

252
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:53,060
Be honest with me.

253
00:24:53,340 --> 00:24:54,780
Is it true or not?

254
00:24:55,980 --> 00:24:57,300
It is not happening anymore.

255
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:58,740
Not happening anymore?

256
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:00,500
So you actually attempted it?

257
00:25:01,660 --> 00:25:04,100
You are the captain of the Criminal Police,

258
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:06,700
how could you make
such a rookie mistake?

259
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:08,820
Chief Wang called me last night.

260
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:11,340
We had a long talk

261
00:25:11,340 --> 00:25:12,980
about how to handle this matter.

262
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:14,220
In my opinion,

263
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:15,940
you should take

264
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,700
a short break for now.

265
00:25:18,180 --> 00:25:20,780
Once we get everything cleared up,

266
00:25:21,980 --> 00:25:23,060
you'll get an explanation.

267
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:24,820
You cannot pull me off now.

268
00:25:25,340 --> 00:25:27,100
Cui Wei, this is about discipline.

269
00:25:27,380 --> 00:25:29,420
No one is allowed
to work while under investigation.

270
00:25:29,420 --> 00:25:30,300
You know that.

271
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:31,620
I just found a new lead.

272
00:25:32,290 --> 00:25:35,020
We could crack the case,
and you want to sideline me?

273
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,780
Do not waste any time dealing with me.

274
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:38,940
I'll accept my punishment.

275
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:40,140
I can write a self-criticism.

276
00:25:40,140 --> 00:25:41,620
But, do not pull me off now.

277
00:25:42,740 --> 00:25:43,900
Stop right there.

278
00:25:44,660 --> 00:25:46,820
So, you do know
this is a critical time for the case.

279
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:48,540
And you just had to

280
00:25:48,540 --> 00:25:50,180
mess it all up now!

281
00:25:50,580 --> 00:25:51,780
You think we want this?

282
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:53,340
You think this is what we hoped for?

283
00:25:53,780 --> 00:25:54,820
Your father-in-law...

